1
00:03:39,553 --> 00:03:40,387
No.

2
00:03:40,846 --> 00:03:41,722
Nothing yet.

3
00:03:43,265 --> 00:03:47,102
Yes, sir, we are looking
everywhere for him.

4
00:03:50,356 --> 00:03:52,107
I'm about to talk with
the lead now, though.

5
00:03:54,193 --> 00:03:55,110
Mm.

6
00:04:02,451 --> 00:04:03,494
God, please…

7
00:04:03,953 --> 00:04:04,828
Please help me.

8
00:04:05,579 --> 00:04:06,538
Please…

9
00:04:06,664 --> 00:04:07,498
Oh!

10
00:04:09,917 --> 00:04:11,710
Please, I'm begging you.

11
00:05:57,024 --> 00:05:58,108
The line.

12
00:05:58,233 --> 00:06:00,277
Come on, baby, come on,
run like the wind, move.

13
00:06:04,073 --> 00:06:05,074
What's going on with the TV?

14
00:06:05,199 --> 00:06:07,076
-What's going around here? Josey!
-Crap!

15
00:06:07,201 --> 00:06:08,827
Hey, look, if we go
to Big George's,

16
00:06:08,952 --> 00:06:09,870
maybe we get that big satellite--

17
00:06:09,995 --> 00:06:11,497
Big George, what?

18
00:06:11,622 --> 00:06:12,998
Big George is a
good 30 miles away.

19
00:06:13,123 --> 00:06:14,124
And cut it with that.

20
00:06:14,249 --> 00:06:15,667
Besides, does Big
George serve you

21
00:06:15,793 --> 00:06:17,377
a very special
Montecassino Birra?

22
00:06:17,586 --> 00:06:18,921
-No, uh--
-Does Big George serve

23
00:06:19,046 --> 00:06:20,631
the best damn hot
wings in the county?

24
00:06:20,881 --> 00:06:22,132
Well, I do love
those damn wings.

25
00:06:22,257 --> 00:06:23,258
Yes, you do.

26
00:06:23,550 --> 00:06:25,302
The internet will go back.

27
00:06:25,427 --> 00:06:27,137
It always does. Relax.

28
00:06:27,596 --> 00:06:28,680
Okay, so the vehicle moves
from rest at the speed

29
00:06:28,806 --> 00:06:30,099
of 25 meters per second.

30
00:06:32,059 --> 00:06:33,435
You gotta be kidding me.

31
00:06:34,186 --> 00:06:35,270
Come on, man, stock the shelves

32
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:36,688
and get your head
outta that thing.

33
00:06:39,149 --> 00:06:40,567
How many times I gotta tell you?

34
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:43,362
And Chase, this is your job.

35
00:06:46,073 --> 00:06:47,116
This is my job.

36
00:06:57,709 --> 00:06:58,752
What good does an education do

37
00:06:58,877 --> 00:07:00,462
if you just work a deadbeat…

38
00:07:02,798 --> 00:07:03,757
job?

39
00:07:04,842 --> 00:07:05,801
It's great.

40
00:07:06,135 --> 00:07:07,094
It makes sense.

41
00:07:12,808 --> 00:07:13,767
Be good.

42
00:07:20,858 --> 00:07:22,317
We're outta Red Bull again.

43
00:07:25,070 --> 00:07:26,613
I'm sorry, my dad
forgot to order it.

44
00:07:26,738 --> 00:07:28,157
It won't be here
until next week.

45
00:07:29,366 --> 00:07:30,200
Alright.

46
00:07:39,209 --> 00:07:40,627
You mixed your vectors up here.

47
00:07:42,087 --> 00:07:42,921
What?

48
00:07:44,882 --> 00:07:45,716
What?

49
00:07:47,009 --> 00:07:48,719
That it should go right there.

50
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:02,149
You're right.

51
00:08:02,816 --> 00:08:03,692
Yeah.

52
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:09,114
Cheeky, is your
internet working?

53
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:10,324
Yeah. Why?

54
00:08:10,449 --> 00:08:12,284
The game just went out. It's a mess.

55
00:08:12,409 --> 00:08:13,493
They're gonna slit my throat.

56
00:08:15,746 --> 00:08:16,705
Hey.

57
00:08:22,544 --> 00:08:23,670
Um, I'll figure it out.

58
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:25,923
I don't know. Gotta go.

59
00:08:35,515 --> 00:08:36,975
Kenny says we jump in the truck,

60
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:38,936
and we have to go all the way down.
What is it, 30 miles?

61
00:08:39,061 --> 00:08:40,562
I feel like it's a "Poltergeist".
It's gonna run

62
00:08:40,687 --> 00:08:42,314
out of the TV and
hit me in the head

63
00:08:42,439 --> 00:08:43,315
I'm just sayin' bud.

64
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:45,108
Gotta watch this. I got
a football game here.

65
00:08:45,234 --> 00:08:46,652
I gotta still settle
up and all that…

66
00:08:46,777 --> 00:08:48,528
Hey, calm down, this
round's on the house.

67
00:08:49,988 --> 00:08:52,032
-Alright.
-Well, that changes things.

68
00:08:52,532 --> 00:08:53,784
Two yards shy…

69
00:08:54,660 --> 00:08:55,953
We got the big one, we got it.

70
00:09:03,168 --> 00:09:04,628
And Stuart will throw.

71
00:09:06,755 --> 00:09:07,589
You fixed it?

72
00:09:08,173 --> 00:09:09,716
Was that you?

73
00:09:13,095 --> 00:09:13,929
I…

74
00:09:15,013 --> 00:09:15,847
yeah.

75
00:09:15,973 --> 00:09:17,224
Well, you saved my ass.

76
00:09:18,016 --> 00:09:20,143
The least I can do
is buy you a drink.

77
00:09:20,477 --> 00:09:22,312
-What's your poison?
-I gotta get back.

78
00:09:22,437 --> 00:09:25,440
Come on, everyone loves
alcohol and football.

79
00:09:25,816 --> 00:09:26,775
This round here.

80
00:09:27,901 --> 00:09:29,361
Okay, I know we don't
follow their rules,

81
00:09:29,486 --> 00:09:32,114
but as a fellow
alien in this town,

82
00:09:32,364 --> 00:09:33,824
I deserve to know your mission.

83
00:09:35,742 --> 00:09:37,828
I got my own secrets.
Let's negotiate.

84
00:09:39,329 --> 00:09:40,330
Where are you from?

85
00:09:40,956 --> 00:09:41,915
Where are you from?

86
00:09:45,002 --> 00:09:48,213
Ay, you come by
every other Sunday,

87
00:09:48,338 --> 00:09:50,173
if not for the game,
then what, confession?

88
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,927
What, are you
keeping tabs on me?

89
00:09:54,886 --> 00:09:56,263
Not much happening around here.

90
00:09:56,388 --> 00:09:58,765
Look, I live out of town a ways.

91
00:09:59,558 --> 00:10:02,436
I gotta come in once in a
while for these supplies.

92
00:10:04,479 --> 00:10:05,314
Okay.

93
00:10:07,733 --> 00:10:08,692
That's…

94
00:10:09,985 --> 00:10:10,944
Maybe next time?

95
00:10:11,903 --> 00:10:12,821
Drinks on me.

96
00:10:25,292 --> 00:10:26,376
Toilet paper?

97
00:10:27,586 --> 00:10:28,503
Really?

98
00:10:29,046 --> 00:10:30,005
Jesus Christ.

99
00:10:42,851 --> 00:10:45,270
And we have scanned
Europe, Asia…

100
00:10:45,562 --> 00:10:46,396
Asia!

101
00:10:47,522 --> 00:10:48,982
Jack didn't go to Asia.

102
00:10:49,733 --> 00:10:51,443
You barely get him to
come into the office

103
00:10:51,568 --> 00:10:52,694
when I used to work with him.

104
00:10:53,153 --> 00:10:54,654
Look, we've talked about this.

105
00:10:54,946 --> 00:10:56,990
The reason his passport's
being flagged is he wants you

106
00:10:57,115 --> 00:10:58,700
to think he's left the country.

107
00:10:59,409 --> 00:11:01,787
Probably gave it to somebody
to transit internationally.

108
00:11:02,079 --> 00:11:05,123
Here he's tapped into the
Customs Department network.

109
00:11:10,045 --> 00:11:13,131
So you think he's
here in the States?

110
00:11:14,841 --> 00:11:15,926
It's not where I'd hide.

111
00:11:16,843 --> 00:11:20,806
But Jack, he's not really
the exotic type, is he?

112
00:11:21,807 --> 00:11:24,142
He's more of a Red Bull,

113
00:11:24,559 --> 00:11:27,020
dirt bike, paranoid
prepper type.

114
00:11:27,813 --> 00:11:30,982
Hey, put your satellites
on the Southeast, okay?

115
00:11:31,108 --> 00:11:32,442
And I mean, deep in the bayou,

116
00:11:32,609 --> 00:11:35,946
one of those shit dirt
towns where nobody visits

117
00:11:36,071 --> 00:11:37,364
and everybody minds
their own business.

118
00:11:37,489 --> 00:11:38,448
You'll find him.

119
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:43,954
Belcor is fixated
on his golden boy.

120
00:11:44,246 --> 00:11:46,331
He wants him back and quick.

121
00:11:46,456 --> 00:11:47,374
It doesn't matter.

122
00:11:47,499 --> 00:11:49,251
I'm heading the
program up now, Marcus.

123
00:11:49,668 --> 00:11:50,585
That's…

124
00:11:50,836 --> 00:11:52,671
-that's not what I hear.
-Hmm.

125
00:11:52,796 --> 00:11:55,674
Belcor made a deal with
our Italian friends,

126
00:11:55,882 --> 00:11:58,844
promised them a working
design six months ago.

127
00:12:01,054 --> 00:12:02,013
I'll find him.

128
00:12:03,765 --> 00:12:04,724
You'll find him?

129
00:12:06,268 --> 00:12:07,727
Not if he finds you first.

130
00:12:10,105 --> 00:12:11,022
Good.

131
00:12:59,863 --> 00:13:00,822
Yeah.

132
00:15:18,126 --> 00:15:19,085
Rook…

133
00:15:21,630 --> 00:15:22,505
to A5.

134
00:15:35,518 --> 00:15:36,519
Goddammit.

135
00:15:55,955 --> 00:15:56,831
Okay.

136
00:16:04,255 --> 00:16:05,131
Anything?

137
00:16:05,590 --> 00:16:07,008
Satellites came up empty.

138
00:16:07,884 --> 00:16:10,762
So Ranish is full of it.

139
00:16:11,805 --> 00:16:12,639
Maybe not.

140
00:16:13,348 --> 00:16:16,309
Someone ordered an Nvidia
A100 graphics card.

141
00:16:16,851 --> 00:16:18,895
Six months ago, one was
shipped to a PO Box,

142
00:16:19,270 --> 00:16:20,438
Memphis, Tennessee.

143
00:16:20,814 --> 00:16:22,440
Name on it. Get this…

144
00:16:23,775 --> 00:16:24,776
Guy Smith.

145
00:16:32,075 --> 00:16:36,413
Get me locations on any
towns in that region,

146
00:16:36,538 --> 00:16:40,834
every asset, every eye
in the sky in this…

147
00:16:44,504 --> 00:16:46,881
And get me on the next flight!

148
00:16:53,513 --> 00:16:54,723
Alright. Alright.

149
00:19:30,879 --> 00:19:31,754
Excuse me.

150
00:19:46,769 --> 00:19:47,729
Need help?

151
00:19:53,318 --> 00:19:54,152
Oh.

152
00:19:55,028 --> 00:19:56,487
I'm not from around here.

153
00:19:56,821 --> 00:19:57,780
Yeah.

154
00:19:58,239 --> 00:19:59,365
Yeah, I figured.

155
00:20:01,784 --> 00:20:04,454
You figured what exactly?

156
00:20:07,165 --> 00:20:10,168
Well, nobody from around here
rocks clothes like that, so.

157
00:20:15,965 --> 00:20:17,050
The sharp eye.

158
00:20:18,509 --> 00:20:19,969
No, I'm just um…

159
00:20:21,721 --> 00:20:22,680
passing through.

160
00:20:24,307 --> 00:20:26,517
Looking for a place to stay.

161
00:20:29,479 --> 00:20:30,939
You know any good places?

162
00:20:32,941 --> 00:20:33,900
There's just one.

163
00:20:34,025 --> 00:20:35,526
There's a bed and
breakfast down the street.

164
00:20:36,945 --> 00:20:38,279
Josey and her family run it.

165
00:20:38,696 --> 00:20:39,906
Josey runs the Rocking Horse.

166
00:20:40,823 --> 00:20:41,783
Bed and breakfast.

167
00:20:41,908 --> 00:20:43,117
-Yeah.
-Down the street.

168
00:20:44,202 --> 00:20:45,036
Yeah.

169
00:20:57,799 --> 00:20:59,092
I'll get you on the next one.

170
00:21:14,524 --> 00:21:16,484
Okay, we're ready.

171
00:21:17,652 --> 00:21:19,946
Welcome to the Land
of Hospitality.

172
00:21:20,071 --> 00:21:22,240
I am Josefina, everybody
calls me Josey.

173
00:21:22,615 --> 00:21:26,995
And this is your temporary home.

174
00:21:27,662 --> 00:21:30,790
It's our little slice of
Latino flavor in town.

175
00:21:31,499 --> 00:21:32,750
Your room is up the stairs.

176
00:21:33,376 --> 00:21:35,044
Are you okay, are you
looking for anything?

177
00:21:35,169 --> 00:21:37,046
Can I help you with
something or…?

178
00:21:38,339 --> 00:21:39,298
All good?

179
00:21:39,590 --> 00:21:40,550
-Okay.
-Okay.

180
00:21:44,804 --> 00:21:45,763
Here's your room.

181
00:21:48,016 --> 00:21:49,017
Be my guest.

182
00:21:51,019 --> 00:21:51,978
How long are you staying?

183
00:21:52,437 --> 00:21:53,312
I'll let you know.

184
00:21:53,771 --> 00:21:54,731
What?

185
00:22:02,989 --> 00:22:04,198
You need anything, let me know.

186
00:22:24,135 --> 00:22:25,011
What's all this?

187
00:22:25,636 --> 00:22:26,471
Oh…

188
00:22:28,014 --> 00:22:29,015
