189
00:22:30,850 --> 00:22:31,851
What do you need that for?

190
00:22:34,687 --> 00:22:37,315
Getting recordings of the
tree growth in the area.

191
00:22:38,191 --> 00:22:39,400
I'm with the
Department of Interior.

192
00:22:39,525 --> 00:22:40,693
I got my ID right here.

193
00:22:41,277 --> 00:22:44,197
Your trees are full of disease.

194
00:22:44,447 --> 00:22:46,491
Yeah, the feds are going
all high tech, huh?

195
00:22:46,991 --> 00:22:48,284
You could say
something like that.

196
00:22:48,409 --> 00:22:50,703
We've been begging
for a bigger budget.

197
00:22:51,412 --> 00:22:52,246
Begging.

198
00:22:52,580 --> 00:22:54,749
And look at all the little
toys you got over here.

199
00:22:54,874 --> 00:22:57,502
Ah, I feel you, sheriff. I do.

200
00:22:57,627 --> 00:23:01,089
We are understaffed and
overworked all the same.

201
00:23:02,465 --> 00:23:04,759
I can't remember the last
time I had a day off.

202
00:23:04,884 --> 00:23:05,885
Can you?

203
00:23:06,010 --> 00:23:06,886
I remember.

204
00:23:13,643 --> 00:23:15,520
How much help you got out here?

205
00:23:21,734 --> 00:23:25,321
If you need anything,
you give us a call.

206
00:23:27,740 --> 00:23:28,741
You have a nice day.

207
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:33,037
Let's go.

208
00:23:59,856 --> 00:24:01,816
Okay, I need a second opin…

209
00:24:02,316 --> 00:24:03,526
Here you go.

210
00:24:04,152 --> 00:24:04,986
Hot and fresh

211
00:24:05,111 --> 00:24:06,070
-for my little nerd.
-Thank you.

212
00:24:06,195 --> 00:24:07,905
You have to feed the brain too.

213
00:24:08,531 --> 00:24:09,365
Oye.

214
00:24:09,490 --> 00:24:10,366
It's so good.

215
00:24:11,159 --> 00:24:13,119
That weirdo with the egg, I
saw him come through here.

216
00:24:13,244 --> 00:24:14,162
-He came here.
-Yeah.

217
00:24:14,287 --> 00:24:15,246
-Yeah.
-What's up?

218
00:24:15,413 --> 00:24:16,247
He didn't even pay.

219
00:24:16,372 --> 00:24:17,456
-He just left.
-Excuse me.

220
00:24:17,582 --> 00:24:18,499
He's trouble.

221
00:24:18,624 --> 00:24:20,418
Trouble? He's an asshole, is what he is.

222
00:24:24,213 --> 00:24:25,256
I don't understand you.

223
00:24:25,756 --> 00:24:27,258
-Okay.
-I don't understand.

224
00:24:27,383 --> 00:24:29,719
Literally, he shut
the door on my face.

225
00:24:29,844 --> 00:24:31,053
He shut the door on your face?

226
00:24:31,470 --> 00:24:32,305
In my…

227
00:24:32,430 --> 00:24:34,098
He went like this, you know
what I'm talking about.

228
00:24:34,223 --> 00:24:35,057
-Oh yeah.
-He was just rude.

229
00:24:35,183 --> 00:24:36,893
He was disrespectful.
Was he mean to you?

230
00:24:38,352 --> 00:24:39,687
-How was he?
-No, he was just,

231
00:24:39,812 --> 00:24:40,980
he was acting really weird.

232
00:24:41,105 --> 00:24:42,064
Creepy is what he is.

233
00:24:42,190 --> 00:24:44,108
-He is creepy.
-God! Yeah, I don't like him.

234
00:24:47,612 --> 00:24:48,821
How are things back there?

235
00:24:49,530 --> 00:24:50,406
What's going on?

236
00:24:54,952 --> 00:24:56,537
If I get that scholarship, I'm gone.

237
00:24:58,039 --> 00:24:59,874
Not looking back.
Thank you for the food.

238
00:25:08,299 --> 00:25:10,009
-Hey, you guys.
-Are you serious?

239
00:25:17,391 --> 00:25:19,352
Jesus Christ.

240
00:25:39,747 --> 00:25:40,706
Gotta calculate, huh?

241
00:25:43,167 --> 00:25:44,377
You scared the crap outta me.

242
00:25:45,503 --> 00:25:47,338
Yeah, it's… This stuff is hard.

243
00:25:47,546 --> 00:25:48,506
Yeah.

244
00:25:50,174 --> 00:25:51,133
You need some help?

245
00:25:55,596 --> 00:25:56,597
Now you gotta take that number.

246
00:25:56,722 --> 00:25:58,391
Break it down. Split it up.

247
00:25:58,557 --> 00:25:59,767
No, split. Yeah, split that.

248
00:26:00,017 --> 00:26:01,352
-Like this.
-There you go.

249
00:26:02,395 --> 00:26:03,229
Oh.

250
00:26:03,813 --> 00:26:05,022
Look at the big brain on you.

251
00:26:08,526 --> 00:26:10,778
Alright. It's just step by step.

252
00:26:18,327 --> 00:26:19,287
So what's new?

253
00:26:21,414 --> 00:26:22,748
Anything ever go
on in this town?

254
00:26:26,836 --> 00:26:29,380
Actually, this asshole came in
looking for a place to stay.

255
00:26:29,922 --> 00:26:31,424
Had beady eyes,
looked kind of creepy.

256
00:26:33,926 --> 00:26:35,303
