-Yeah.

257
00:26:36,679 --> 00:26:38,097
It was probably just a tourist.

258
00:26:40,141 --> 00:26:41,392
Tourists never
just show up here.

259
00:26:42,393 --> 00:26:43,602
Well, maybe it was an illegal

260
00:26:44,395 --> 00:26:45,896
in search of the American dream.

261
00:26:48,232 --> 00:26:49,734
Either way, it's probably best to

262
00:26:51,986 --> 00:26:53,029
trust your instincts.

263
00:26:58,617 --> 00:26:59,702
You let me know if
you need any help.

264
00:27:00,411 --> 00:27:01,370
I will.

265
00:27:05,416 --> 00:27:06,625
Thank you for the help.

266
00:27:48,501 --> 00:27:50,586
The man who was just in here,

267
00:27:51,629 --> 00:27:52,588
do you know him?

268
00:27:54,340 --> 00:27:57,385
-Who?
-Boy, what are you, a fucking owl?

269
00:27:58,803 --> 00:28:01,639
That guy with, uh, a beard.

270
00:28:04,141 --> 00:28:05,935
Beards are kind of in
fashion these days.

271
00:28:06,435 --> 00:28:07,603
Don't…

272
00:28:08,813 --> 00:28:11,315
I just saw him leave.

273
00:28:13,526 --> 00:28:14,777
A lot of people come in here.

274
00:28:20,282 --> 00:28:23,119
So a lot of people come in here.

275
00:28:24,662 --> 00:28:25,579
Now…

276
00:28:26,747 --> 00:28:30,418
you seem like a smart kid.

277
00:28:32,670 --> 00:28:33,838
Stop fucking around.

278
00:28:34,713 --> 00:28:37,299
I am pretty smart.
I got a 1580 on that SAT, so--

279
00:28:39,593 --> 00:28:40,428
Talk.

280
00:28:42,513 --> 00:28:43,431
Uh…

281
00:28:43,764 --> 00:28:44,723
Okay, okay.

282
00:28:45,933 --> 00:28:47,226
There's a guy that
comes in here sometimes.

283
00:28:47,351 --> 00:28:48,227
He buys supplies.

284
00:28:48,352 --> 00:28:49,311
He lives somewhere off the grid.

285
00:28:50,479 --> 00:28:51,564
That's all I know. Okay?

286
00:28:52,857 --> 00:28:53,691
Okay!

287
00:29:00,072 --> 00:29:01,449
If I find out

288
00:29:02,700 --> 00:29:03,659
you know more,

289
00:29:05,035 --> 00:29:05,870
I'll be back.

290
00:29:07,037 --> 00:29:07,997
And next time,

291
00:29:09,290 --> 00:29:10,124
well…

292
00:29:12,710 --> 00:29:14,336
you know what happens
if I come back.

293
00:29:16,046 --> 00:29:17,006
You're a smart kid.

294
00:29:17,590 --> 00:29:19,717
You got 1580 on your SAT.

295
00:29:21,177 --> 00:29:22,052
Chase.

296
00:29:24,805 --> 00:29:26,348
Delivery guy out back. Give me a hand.

297
00:29:29,852 --> 00:29:31,312
Anything else I can
help you with, sir?

298
00:30:19,109 --> 00:30:20,986
Bobby , you're finally back.

299
00:30:21,111 --> 00:30:23,072
Oh my God, where
were you? Please.

300
00:30:28,494 --> 00:30:31,038
Marcus, I picked up a highly
active wireless signal

301
00:30:31,163 --> 00:30:33,541
coming from an area near you
that has been uninhabitable

302
00:30:33,666 --> 00:30:35,459
for the last 20 years.

303
00:30:35,834 --> 00:30:37,086
I attached the location.

304
00:31:25,676 --> 00:31:26,635
Alright, fellas.

305
00:31:27,219 --> 00:31:28,971
Target's supposed to be
brought back alive, okay?

306
00:31:29,847 --> 00:31:30,848
Alive!

307
00:31:31,807 --> 00:31:32,725
Rock salt only.

308
00:31:32,850 --> 00:31:34,435
So we're going after
some Oppenheimer wannabe?

309
00:31:34,643 --> 00:31:35,603
Just focus.

310
00:31:36,562 --> 00:31:37,396
Hey Marcus.

311
00:31:37,938 --> 00:31:40,316
He's eight miles
south of Marker 52.

312
00:31:44,111 --> 00:31:45,029
How'd you find him?

313
00:31:47,906 --> 00:31:50,075
These are the best guys you got?

314
00:31:50,784 --> 00:31:51,869
These are the best
guys I could get

315
00:31:51,994 --> 00:31:52,911
in short notice, Marcus.

316
00:31:53,037 --> 00:31:54,705
I got two more guys
blocking the street.

317
00:32:01,170 --> 00:32:02,046
Alright, guys, let's go.

318
00:32:02,212 --> 00:32:03,130
Come on, let's go.

319
00:32:03,714 --> 00:32:04,548
Load it up.

320
00:32:12,222 --> 00:32:14,808
Excuse me, sir, but someone
has bypassed the firewall

321
00:32:14,933 --> 00:32:16,435
and accessed the
employee tracker.

322
00:32:16,852 --> 00:32:17,770
How do you know?

323
00:32:17,936 --> 00:32:20,773
Because there's multiple logins
from a former employee account.

324
00:32:21,231 --> 00:32:22,775
We're on it. I'll keep you updated.

325
00:32:23,359 --> 00:32:24,360
Yeah, sure.

326
00:32:28,530 --> 00:32:31,700
Have security
confiscate every phone,

327
00:32:31,867 --> 00:32:33,619
every fucking computer.

328
00:32:34,662 --> 00:32:35,704
We've been hacked.

329
00:32:36,413 --> 00:32:37,748
I'll get on it right away, sir.

330
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:39,833
Also, Ranish is waiting
outside for you.

331
00:32:39,958 --> 00:32:41,001
Have him waiting.

332
00:32:43,045 --> 00:32:44,046
Shit!

333
00:32:46,173 --> 00:32:49,218
Why is this happening to me?

334
00:33:18,080 --> 00:33:19,039
Now.

335
00:33:31,635 --> 00:33:33,303
Alright, look out, here we go.

336
00:33:35,556 --> 00:33:37,015
Move forward. Forward now.

337
00:33:38,434 --> 00:33:39,435
I see you.

338
00:33:43,021 --> 00:33:43,939
Oh, shit.

339
00:33:53,323 --> 00:33:55,868
What the hell? These lights.

340
00:33:56,744 --> 00:33:57,703
Why are these here?

341
00:34:07,171 --> 00:34:08,088
What the fuck?

342
00:34:09,923 --> 00:34:10,966
Don't touch me!

343
00:34:29,359 --> 00:34:31,403
Move it. Get through.

344
00:34:31,528 --> 00:34:33,030
Go, go, go!

345
00:34:33,322 --> 00:34:34,907
Marcus. Come on, let's go.

346
00:34:53,091 --> 00:34:53,967
Oh, shit.

347
00:35:01,850 --> 00:35:02,893
Oh, shit!

348
00:35:03,018 --> 00:35:04,061
Landmine.

349
00:35:05,938 --> 00:35:06,897
Come on, toss it.

350
00:35:07,189 --> 00:35:08,357
Toss me the weapon.

351
00:35:09,858 --> 00:35:10,818
Smoke grenade.

352
00:35:11,235 --> 00:35:12,653
Smoke grenade. Smoke him out.

353
00:35:16,865 --> 00:35:17,825
Do it!

354
00:35:18,700 --> 00:35:21,203
Throw in the fucking smoke.

355
00:35:32,381 --> 00:35:33,298
Holy shit!

356
00:35:34,091 --> 00:35:34,925
Hold your breath!

357
00:35:35,050 --> 00:35:36,301
Up, on your feet!

358
00:35:36,593 --> 00:35:38,178
Let's go! Come on!

359
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:40,472
On your feet! Let's go!

360
00:35:42,099 --> 00:35:44,101
We don't leave until we get him!

361
00:35:44,268 --> 00:35:45,978
Fuck you! You go in
there and get him!

362
00:36:37,696 --> 00:36:40,365
I told you, you're
not leaving here.

363
00:36:41,158 --> 00:36:42,367
We're hired help.

364
00:36:47,039 --> 00:36:48,040
You're on your own now.

365
00:37:03,931 --> 00:37:05,349
Yeah, yeah. I get it.

366
00:37:06,600 --> 00:37:08,936
I just want some good
news for a change.

367
00:37:09,102 --> 00:37:11,146
He knew we were coming.

368
00:37:11,355 --> 00:37:13,148
He wiped out the entire team.

369
00:37:13,607 --> 00:37:15,400
That's not fucking good news.

370
00:37:24,368 --> 00:37:25,911
Get Ranish in here.

371
00:37:26,453 --> 00:37:27,371
Yes, sir.

372
00:38:17,796 --> 00:38:19,381
Hey. Hey, that's him, right?

373
00:38:21,299 --> 00:38:22,259
That's him!

374
00:38:22,551 --> 00:38:23,885
Go, go, go! Let's go!

375
00:39:19,816 --> 00:39:21,234
Sorry. I was
across the street.

376
00:39:21,359 --> 00:39:22,319
What's so urgent?

377
00:39:23,570 --> 00:39:24,863
Come in, close the door.

378
00:39:27,657 --> 00:39:29,951
First of all, we've been hacked.

379
00:39:30,744 --> 00:39:32,829
All the information's
leaked out.

380
00:39:33,830 --> 00:39:35,957
And I don't fucking
care, we might be bugged.

381
00:39:36,083 --> 00:39:37,834
People might hear
what we're saying.

382
00:39:38,794 --> 00:39:41,713
And your friend Jack,

383
00:39:42,756 --> 00:39:45,300
he's been located…

384
00:39:45,425 --> 00:39:47,969
Let me guess, some
forgotten town

385
00:39:48,095 --> 00:39:50,013
in the southeastern part
of the United States.

386
00:39:53,517 --> 00:39:56,061
I always liked you because
you're fucking smart.

387
00:39:56,895 --> 00:39:58,480
-Sit down.
-Thanks.

388
00:39:59,981 --> 00:40:01,650
So, now…

389
00:40:02,984 --> 00:40:05,403
you're smart, so you think,

390
00:40:06,154 --> 00:40:07,405
would it be a possibility

391
00:40:07,531 --> 00:40:10,867
to end this project by yourself?

392
00:40:11,368 --> 00:40:12,786
I'll get you any help you need.

393
00:40:12,911 --> 00:40:16,998
I mean, but do you
really need Jack?

394
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:20,168
He would be helpful,

395
00:40:21,795 --> 00:40:23,880
but I taught him most
of what he knows.

396
00:40:25,006 --> 00:40:26,341
Best student I ever had,

397
00:40:26,758 --> 00:40:28,593
figure out and solve
solutions in time

398
00:40:28,718 --> 00:40:30,470
that it'd take most
scientists a decade.

399
00:40:31,179 --> 00:40:32,139
Yeah.

400
00:40:32,973 --> 00:40:36,560
And you think it's
smart stealing research,

401
00:40:38,061 --> 00:40:41,439
research that I
paid millions for.

402
00:40:41,773 --> 00:40:43,525
We always knew he
was a wild card.

403
00:40:43,900 --> 00:40:45,068
He was brought in here

404
00:40:45,193 --> 00:40:48,530
because everyone believed
he could finish this.

405
00:40:49,030 --> 00:40:50,490
Now, it's not my fault

406
00:40:51,032 --> 00:40:54,452
that somebody disclosed your
intention was to weaponize it.

407
00:40:55,287 --> 00:40:58,123
Marcus and his team,
they found him.

408
00:40:59,374 --> 00:41:00,959
Marcus is in the Southeast?

409
00:41:01,585 --> 00:41:02,544
Yep.

410
00:41:05,964 --> 00:41:07,799
He'll come home in a body bag.

411
00:42:50,235 --> 00:42:51,903
Let me go! Let me go!

412
00:42:54,489 --> 00:42:56,241
-What are you doing?
-They found me.

413
00:42:56,366 --> 00:42:57,409
Who found you? What?

414
00:42:57,659 --> 00:42:58,660
The asshole tourist guy?

415
00:42:59,035 --> 00:42:59,911
Yeah.

416
00:43:00,578 --> 00:43:03,873
Look, he works for
my former employer.

417
00:43:03,999 --> 00:43:04,874
What do they want?

418
00:43:05,792 --> 00:43:06,876
It's a long story. Listen.

419
00:43:07,669 --> 00:43:09,671
Have you seen any other
guys like him around here?

420
00:43:09,879 --> 00:43:11,715
No. No, I don't think so.

421
00:43:13,091 --> 00:43:14,050
Well, they're coming.

422
00:43:15,844 --> 00:43:16,928
-Who's coming?
-I gotta go.

423
00:43:17,220 --> 00:43:18,596
Who's coming?
Wait, hold on.

424
00:43:18,722 --> 00:43:19,889
Wait, where are you gonna go?

425
00:43:20,015 --> 00:43:20,849
I'll figure it out.

426
00:43:20,974 --> 00:43:22,434
Wait, hold on, I got
a place you can hide.

427
00:43:22,559 --> 00:43:25,937
It's this war bunker thing.

428
00:43:26,062 --> 00:43:27,105
They used it to hide
weapons from the north

429
00:43:27,230 --> 00:43:28,356
after the end of the war.

430
00:43:28,606 --> 00:43:29,858
-I can show you where it is.
-Well…

431
00:43:30,734 --> 00:43:32,152
does anybody else
know about this place?

432
00:43:33,278 --> 00:43:34,279
No, I don't think so.

433
00:43:34,404 --> 00:43:35,572
It's pretty impossible to find.

434
00:43:36,781 --> 00:43:37,615
I can show you where it is.

435
00:43:37,741 --> 00:43:39,200
-I can go with you.
-No, no. You stay put

436
00:43:39,534 --> 00:43:41,161
and you stay right here.
Do you understand me?

437
00:43:41,286 --> 00:43:44,080
Do not follow me.
These people are extremely dangerous.

438
00:43:47,292 --> 00:43:48,251
Hey.

439
00:43:51,463 --> 00:43:52,839
You're a good kid, Chase.

440
00:43:53,590 --> 00:43:54,924
Stick to your books, alright?

441
00:43:57,761 --> 00:43:58,720
Wait!

442
00:44:25,914 --> 00:44:26,873
I got you.

443
00:44:26,998 --> 00:44:27,832
Come on, come on, come on.

444
00:44:27,957 --> 00:44:29,793
My beer, Amelia.
Quick, quick, quick.

445
00:44:30,543 --> 00:44:31,503
Here you go.

446
00:44:31,628 --> 00:44:33,463
Oh my God, let me take
this out of your way.

447
00:44:33,671 --> 00:44:34,839
Marquito, clean this up.

448
00:44:35,632 --> 00:44:38,593
So sorry for the delay,
your pizza's gonna be right here.

449
00:44:38,885 --> 00:44:39,719
Hey.

450
00:44:39,844 --> 00:44:40,762
-Hey.
-Hey.

451
00:44:41,596 --> 00:44:44,307
I just wanted to tell
you that I'm leaving.

452
00:44:44,432 --> 00:44:46,184
-Leaving. Why?
-Yeah, look, I need you…

453
00:44:46,309 --> 00:44:47,435
It doesn't matter. Okay?

454
00:44:47,560 --> 00:44:49,104
I just need you to keep
looking after Chase.

455
00:44:49,229 --> 00:44:51,064
He's a good kid.
He's got huge potential.

456
00:44:53,942 --> 00:44:57,946
And I just need you to
know that I really wanted

457
00:44:58,071 --> 00:45:00,073
to have that beer with
you and watch the game

458
00:45:00,198 --> 00:45:01,908
and just been able
to sit here with you.

459
00:45:02,534 --> 00:45:03,451
-I keep--
-What is that?

460
00:45:29,018 --> 00:45:29,853
Down there?

461
00:45:29,978 --> 00:45:30,895
-Yeah.
-No.

462
00:45:31,020 --> 00:45:32,897
-Yeah.
-Listen to me, I'm not doing it.

463
00:45:33,022 --> 00:45:34,816
Don't even debate me.

464
00:45:34,941 --> 00:45:35,984
-No, I'm not--
-You're going.

465
00:45:36,109 --> 00:45:39,237
I need somebody who
knows how he thinks

466
00:45:39,404 --> 00:45:41,281
and how he maneuvers out there.

467
00:45:41,406 --> 00:45:42,282
You know I hate the South.

468
00:45:42,407 --> 00:45:44,451
I'm not going down to
those mosquito-infested…

469
00:45:44,576 --> 00:45:46,828
-old country.
-Yes, you are!

470
00:45:48,329 --> 00:45:50,290
And you're going to
get my best strike team

471
00:45:50,415 --> 00:45:51,833
to do all the heavy lifting.

472
00:45:51,958 --> 00:45:54,836
All you gotta do is to
lead them to the target.

473
00:45:54,961 --> 00:45:58,256
I apologize, I don't chase people
around in backcountry woods.

474
00:45:58,381 --> 00:46:02,802
-And I'm not gonna go down--
-Hey! I paid you a fucking fortune!

475
00:46:04,095 --> 00:46:05,638
Now it's time for payback.

476
00:46:06,431 --> 00:46:09,517
You get out there
and you get him

477
00:46:09,726 --> 00:46:11,478
and you bring him back to me.

478
00:46:11,644 --> 00:46:12,520
Okay?

479
00:46:19,527 --> 00:46:21,404
Go run to my house,
and get my bag packed.

480
00:46:21,529 --> 00:46:22,489
No need.

481
00:46:23,406 --> 00:46:24,741
The bag is packed.

482
00:46:25,700 --> 00:46:27,410
You're leaving right now.

483
00:46:36,044 --> 00:46:37,212
Break a leg, pal.

484
00:47:08,201 --> 00:47:09,827
I don't need you here.

485
00:47:16,751 --> 00:47:17,710
Marcus.

486
00:47:19,045 --> 00:47:20,672
I thought you'd be dead by now.

487
00:47:22,674 --> 00:47:24,384
Just tell me all the
ways it went wrong.

488
00:47:27,220 --> 00:47:29,889
It was an ambush.

489
00:47:30,265 --> 00:47:33,434
Whole team was taken
out by booby traps.

490
00:47:33,601 --> 00:47:35,562
How was it an ambush if
you were going after him?

491
00:47:37,230 --> 00:47:40,525
This, this is your mess now.

492
00:47:40,817 --> 00:47:42,819
I'm just working cleanup.

493
00:47:44,028 --> 00:47:46,823
-What's your plan?
-Oh no. No, this is our mess.

494
00:47:47,156 --> 00:47:48,908
And it's very simple.
We're gonna go to his place.

495
00:47:49,033 --> 00:47:50,827
We're gonna salvage
all of his research.

496
00:47:50,952 --> 00:47:52,579
We're gonna find it and
bring him back to Belcor.

497
00:47:52,704 --> 00:47:53,663
Simple as that.

498
00:47:54,831 --> 00:47:57,083
-Just the two of us?
-No.

499
00:47:57,458 --> 00:47:59,544
Belcor has lost complete
confidence in you.

500
00:48:00,044 --> 00:48:01,671
No, he sent in the private team.

501
00:48:01,796 --> 00:48:03,172
They'll be here in two hours.

502
00:48:03,798 --> 00:48:04,757
Look on the bright side,

503
00:48:04,882 --> 00:48:06,634
they're gonna have another
shot at the golden boy.

504
00:48:07,093 --> 00:48:07,927
Hey!

505
00:48:08,219 --> 00:48:09,345
How's the scouting going?

506
00:48:09,470 --> 00:48:11,222
You getting your shots, Spielberg?

507
00:48:13,891 --> 00:48:15,935
It's great, Sheriff.

508
00:48:16,352 --> 00:48:18,563
Who's your new sidekick, director?

509
00:48:20,607 --> 00:48:24,777
I had to call in some extra hands.

510
00:48:25,028 --> 00:48:27,405
-What'd you say?
-Some extra hands.

511
00:48:29,032 --> 00:48:31,409
You're very lucky to have him, sir.
He's a uh…

512
00:48:32,285 --> 00:48:34,454
He's a real auteur,
real Robert Bresson.

513
00:48:35,079 --> 00:48:36,247
Huh, outstanding.

514
00:48:38,583 --> 00:48:40,960
Y'all need anything,
I'll be right here.

515
00:48:41,878 --> 00:48:43,129
Have a nice night.

516
00:48:44,088 --> 00:48:45,381
You do the same, Sheriff.

517
00:48:46,466 --> 00:48:47,300
Hey, hey.

518
00:48:47,467 --> 00:48:49,427
How many more people
coming to my town?

519
00:48:50,803 --> 00:48:52,263
Just be a few of us, Sheriff.

520
00:48:54,724 --> 00:48:56,559
You have really
fucked this up, huh?

521
00:48:57,060 --> 00:48:58,603
Don't worry about it.

522
00:48:59,020 --> 00:49:01,606
The whole town has
that deaf bastard,

523
00:49:01,731 --> 00:49:04,275
and a deputy looks like
he's 18 looking after it.

524
00:49:06,611 --> 00:49:07,737
I'm not staying there.

525
00:49:08,988 --> 00:49:09,906
Oh.

526
00:49:10,698 --> 00:49:11,741
Stay in your car then.

527
00:49:48,194 --> 00:49:49,570
No! Let go!

528
00:49:50,363 --> 00:49:51,739
Chase, what the fuck
are you doing here?

529
00:49:53,282 --> 00:49:55,118
-What the fuck are you doing here?
-I knew you'd found it.

530
00:49:55,243 --> 00:49:56,119
I told you…

531
00:49:56,244 --> 00:49:57,662
-not to follow me.
-I know what you said.

532
00:49:57,787 --> 00:49:58,996
-Did anybody see you come up here?
-No!

533
00:49:59,122 --> 00:50:01,541
-Nobody followed me. I made sure.
-Goddammit.

534
00:50:03,543 --> 00:50:05,670
I brought you your supplies
from the store,

535
00:50:05,795 --> 00:50:06,713
the stuff you usually get.

536
00:50:15,471 --> 00:50:18,599
Oh my God, you gotta stop
sneaking up on me like that.

537
00:50:18,725 --> 00:50:19,600
Jesus!

538
